    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 pork loin cutlets</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>2 large eggs, beaten</li>
            <li>1 cup panko breadcrumbs</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil, for frying</li>
            <li>Cabbage, shredded (for serving)</li>
            <li>Tonkatsu sauce (store-bought or homemade) for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Tonkatsu</li>
            <li>Japanese</li>
            <li>Pork</li>
            <li>Main Course</li>
            <li>Crispy</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Season the pork cutlets with salt and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Dredge each cutlet in flour, dip into beaten eggs, and coat with panko breadcrumbs, pressing the breadcrumbs onto the cutlets to adhere.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Fry the pork cutlets until golden brown and cooked through, about 4-5 minutes per side.</li>
            <li>Transfer the tonkatsu to a cutting board and let them rest for a minute. Slice each cutlet into strips.</li>
            <li>Serve tonkatsu over a bed of shredded cabbage and drizzle with tonkatsu sauce.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious homemade Tonkatsu!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

